summary:
• FY2025 Results Announcement Date: 21 August 2025.
  • Annual Report Publication Date: 30 September 2025.
  • Annual Meeting Date: 13 November 2025 (hybrid online/in-person).

No material financial or operational data disclosed.

Here’s the concise summary of material information from the ASX announcement:

  • FY25 Hydro Generation: 3,410 GWh (17% lower YoY), 4th lowest since 1980 due to 12th percentile Waikato inflows and low Lake Taupō levels.
  • Total FY25 Generation: 7,906 GWh (11% lower YoY), with declines in hydro (-17%), wind (-6%), and geothermal (-2%).
  • Q4 Hydrological Recovery: Waikato catchment inflows rebounded to 79th percentile, improving FY26 storage outlook.
  • Increased Mean Hydro Generation: Uplift to 4,140 GWh/year from FY26 (62 GWh increase) due to Karāpiro rehab and Digital River AI optimization.
  • Karāpiro Project Completion: Third unit replacement finishes Sep-25, adding 16.5MW capacity (+32 GWh/year at average inflows).
  • Market Prices: FY25 Auckland spot average $216/MWh; FY26-27 forwards at $179/MWh (as of 30-Jun-25).

Omitted: Market share stats, operational details without material impact.

Material Information Summary

  • Infratil Limited (IFT) to be added to S&P/ASX 200 Index
  • Effective: Open of trading, Wednesday, 23 July 2025.
  • Spartan Resources (SPR) to be removed from S&P/ASX 200 Index (due to acquisition by Ramelius Resources)
  • Effective: Same date (23 July 2025).

No other material trading or capital markets information identified.

Here's the concise extraction of material information from the Meridian Energy monthly operating report:

Monthly Operating Report (June 2025) Key Points:

  • Hydro Storage:
  • National hydro storage increased from 94% to 104% of historical average (June–14 July 2025)

  • South Island storage: 95% of average; North Island: 150%

  • Generation & Pricing:

  • June 2025 generation: 6.1% higher YoY (hydro/wind increase)

  • Average generation price: 54.2% lower YoY ($121.0/MWh)

  • Retail Performance:

  • Retail sales volumes: +7.9% YoY (June 2025)

  • Customer connections: +9.6% YoY

  • NZAS (Aluminium Smelter):

  • Average load: 530MW (June 2025)

  • Agreement to end demand response by 11 Aug 2025

  • Market Data:

  • Electricity futures prices declined in Q4 2025

  • National demand: +1.4% YoY (June 2025) but -2.6% YoY for Q4

  • Costs:

  • Q4 operating costs: -0.2% YoY
  • Q4 capex: -16.5% YoY

No capital raising, trading halt, or material changes to capital structure identified. Focus on operational metrics affecting energy supply/demand dynamics.
